After a few hours, Tyrael decided it was time to get going. Even 
though he was a techno-organic and thus more resistant than either a 
beast or a machine, it would take him some time to get to the island.

Tyrael: Cheetah, Tigerhawk, I am going. Proceed with the repairs on 
the base and don't leave it until I'm back. Contact me only if there 
is something significant, like someone attacking.

He started flying higher and higher, soaring in the cloudy sky. It was 
cold up there, but he'd seen worse. He went for the island, hoping 
Cygnar will really be there. One thing he had learned is that Preds 
could seldom be trusted, but he hoped Cygnar was different. Else, he 
would have to destroy him too.
